'''Bey al-Mahalla''' ({{lang-ar|بيه المحلّة}}) meaning ''Bey of the Camp'', was a title for the [[heir apparent]] to throne of the [[Tunisia|Beylik of Tunis]]. The title was given to the most senior member of the Beylical family after the reigning [[Bey of Tunis|Bey]]. The title came the style of [[Highness]]. The last person to carry this title was [[Husain Bey, Crown Prince of Tunisia|Prince Husain Bey, Bey al-Mahalla]], heir apparent to Tunisia from 1955 until the abolition of the monarchy in 1957. From Tunisia's independence on March 20, 1956 he was given the new title of Crown Prince.

