{{Infobox language |name=Kakabai |altname=Igora |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region=[[Milne Bay Province]], tip of Cape Vogel |speakers=900 |date=2003 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]] |fam5=[[Papuan Tip languages|Papuan Tip]] |fam6=[[Nuclear Papuan Tip languages|Nuclear Papuan Tip]] |fam7=[[North Papuan Mainland – D'Entrecasteaux languages|North Papuan Mainland – D'Entrecasteaux]] |fam8=Kakabai–Dawawa |iso3=kqf |glotto=kaka1267 |glottorefname=Kakabai }}
'''Kakabai''' is an [[Austronesian]] language spoken in [[Milne Bay Province]] of [[Papua New Guinea]].
== Alphabet == Kakabai language has 20 letters (Aa, Bb, Dd, Ee, Gg, Ḡḡ, Ii, Kk, Ll, Mm, Nn, Oo, Pp, Rr, Ss, Tt, Uu, Vv, Ww, Yy) and 1 [[diphthong]] (kw).
